news.title: YEIDA plans to launch mixed-land scheme for industries & houses on same plot
news.para: While allottees can develop industry on 75% of the land allotted to them, the remaining plot can be used for residential, commercial and even institutional purposes.

news.title: Gurugram: Scanner on large building sites not on pollution portal
news.para: CAQM has directed projects that haven't registered on the portal to shut down operations. Though Gurugram has around 3,000 such sites, only 1% of them has registered on the portal so far.

news.title: Not on portal yet? Constructions at sites are likely to be stopped soon in Noida & Ghaziabad
news.para: Three developers in Noida were fined for violating construction and demolition rules. He said the developers had been told to ensure that the construction materials were covered, water was sprinkled on them and anti-smog guns were used at sites that were over 20,000 sqm in area.

news.title: ED searches premises of Orbit Ventures, others in DHFL case
news.para: It is alleged that DHFL’s erstwhile promoters Kapil Wadhawan and his brother Dheeraj Wadhawan aka Baba Dewan diverted part of the fraud money to Orbit Ventures in the form of loans which turned into non-performing assets.

news.title: Gurugram: Owners de-seal illegal flats, DTCP razes 27 units partially in Palam Vihar
news.para: The enforcement wing of the department of town and country planning (DTCP) on Thursday partially demolished 27 flats in Palam Vihar area after developers and property owners unlocked these units that were sealed by the authorities and started remaining construction again.

news.title: Fresh push from Maharashtra deputy CM for redevelopment projects
news.para: Of the around 1.20 lakh registered cooperative societies and over 80,000 apartments, nearly 60,000 units are over 30-year-old and would want to go for redevelopment.

news.title: About 100 'lapsed' housing projects likely to get showcause notices from MahaRERA
news.para: ​In the first phase, showcause notices have been issued to 19 projects in Mumbai, 6 in Pune, and 14 in rest of the state. The authority has given a month's time to developers to respond to the notices and explain why their projects lapsed.

news.title: Haryana eyeing Rs 1 lakh crore investment for Global City project in Gurugram
news.para: Khattar said that the Global City is a mixed land-use township being developed over nearly 1,080 acres to redefine the concept of urban development and what cities of the future shall look like through its sustainability-focused future-oriented infrastructure planning and design.

news.title: Sebi cancels registration of Brickwork Ratings
news.para: In its order, Sebi highlighted several violations by Brickwork, including that it failed to follow a proper rating process and exercise due diligence while providing ratings.

news.title: Dutch house prices fell 5.8% in third quarter, industry group says
news.para: The Union of Estate Agents (NVM) attributed the decline to rising mortgage rates. Average Dutch interest rates on a 20-year mortgage without state-backed guarantees have risen to 4.3% from about 1.4% late last year.

news.title: Nashik: About 40% streetlights in Ambad industrial area defunct
news.para: The Ambad industrial estate — which is located within the jurisdiction of the Nashik Municipal Corporation (NMC) and houses over 2,000 small, medium and large industrial units — has over 1,500 streetlights.

news.title: Mangaluru: Builder booked for not handing over flats
news.para: Abdul Rahim, a resident of Mupperia village in Sullia, filed a private complaint with the second additional senior civil judge and CJM court, alleging that the builder had not handed over the apartment, even after paying Rs 33 lakh in various phases.

news.title: WeWork India leases 3.62 lakh sq ft office space in two buildings in Bengaluru
news.para: The workspace at Kalyani Roshni Tech Hub spans over 310,000 sq ft. It houses over 5,000 desks spread over eight floors. Embassy One is spread across over 52,000 sq ft with a capacity of over 600 desks across two floors.

news.title: Goa: Rights panel directs cooperative societies body to act on leaky flat
news.para: The commission found that the grievance was being raised with the assistant registrar of cooperative societies since 2018.

news.title: Can Fin Homes mulls raising up to Rs 4,000 crore debt capital
news.para: ​The board of directors of the company is scheduled to meet on October 17, 2022 to approve financial results for the company's second quarter and first half ended September 2022-23.
